# Capitalization Rules for Content

## General Rule
- Only the first word of each heading, paragraph, or text block should be capitalized
- All other words should be in lowercase, except for proper nouns

## Proper Nouns (Always Capitalized)
- Product names (e.g., "Boobie Goods", "MyLineArts")
- Brand names
- Person names (e.g., "Stefanie Szabo")
- Platform names (e.g., "Facebook", "Twitter", "Pinterest")

## Examples of Correct Capitalization
- Headings:
  - "Boobie Goods: o guia completo para desenhos para colorir e imprimir"
  - "O que são Boobie Goods?"
  - "Benefícios dos desenhos para colorir"

- Card Titles:
  - "Arte terapêutica"
  - "Decoração personalizada"
  - "Presentes especiais"

- Dates:
  - "14 de junho, 2025"
  - "20 de março, 2024"

- Instructions:
  - "Como começar"
  - "Dica pro"
  - "Escolha o papel ideal"

## Implementation Notes
- This rule applies to all text content including:
  - Headers (h1, h2, h3, etc.)
  - Paragraphs
  - Card titles
  - List items
  - Button text
  - Footer content
  - Dates and times
  - Instructions and tips 